title: My works
text: Welcome to My works, a platform for engaging conversations and thought-provoking discussions that shape the fabric of our projects. Here, we believe in the power of code to inspire change, foster understanding, and ignite meaningful connections among individuals from all walks of life.

title: Home
text:
This website is made with quarto. Quarto is a multi-language, next-generation version of R Markdown from Posit and includes dozens of new features and capabilities while at the same being able to render most existing Rmd files without modification.
In this tutorial, we'll show you how to use RStudio with Quarto. You'll edit code and markdown in RStudio just as you would with any computational document (e.g., R Markdown) and preview the rendered document in the Viewer tab as you work.
The following is a Quarto document with the extension .qmd (on the left), along with its rendered version as HTML (on the right). You could also choose to render it into other formats like PDF, MS Word, etc.

title: how-to
text: This page is dedicated to breaking down the science behind any phenomenon or substance involves a meticulous examination of its fundamental principles, properties, and interactions at various levels of scale. Whether it’s delving into the molecular structure of a chemical compound, analyzing the biomechanics of a physical process, or exploring the intricate workings of a biological system, scientific inquiry aims to uncover the underlying mechanisms that govern its behavior and characteristics. This often entails experimentation, observation, and theoretical modeling to elucidate the intricate relationships between different components and their roles in shaping the overall phenomenon. Through this systematic approach, scientists can gain a deeper understanding of the intricacies of nature and harness this knowledge to advance various fields, from medicine and technology to environmental science and beyond.

title: About me
text:
I have 4 year Indian classic degree from Malla Reddy Institute Of Engineering & Technology which is affl. To JNTUH, and have involved in many events & won prizes.

Experienced in startups with “No excuses” attitude and would take on-spot challenges. However, working in startups taught me not to stick-on to a particular role, rather be open-minded and flexible to take up any kind of designation to improve organizational excellence.





Jan 2024-May 2026
Master of Science, Data Analytics Engineering
Courses: Big Data to Information, Principles of Data Management and Mining, Analytics and Modelling, Applied Statistics, Machine Learning.



Aug 2019-Jul 2023
Bachelor of technology (BTech), Computer Science and Engineering
Courses: Algorithms and Design, Object Oriented Programming, OS, Compiler Design, Data Structures, Artificial Intelligence, Machine Learning








o    Worked with Development team focusing on Website.
o    Automation: Single handedly developed JSON Test cases for Cypress which reduced human effort per project by 35%.
o   Full Stack: Collaborated in a team of five to build GraphQL reject API to implement Material UI and written Typescript logic for package rejection and approval in vendor app.
o    Data Analysis: To avoid anomalies in test cases, Excel pricing scenario discrepancies were fixed. Obtained data with SQL.
o    Achievements: Won recognition for enrolling corporate hotel to vendor app by meeting & convincing directors. Won opportunity for organizing and managing Jira tickets for co-developers.
